<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Learnings</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/</link><description>Recent content on Learnings</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Atomic File Writes</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/atomic-file-writes/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/atomic-file-writes/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Date:&lt;/strong&gt; 2026-04-09
&lt;strong&gt;Context:&lt;/strong&gt; nanobot session persistence bug&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="problem"&gt;Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Writing files with &lt;code&gt;open(path, &amp;quot;w&amp;quot;)&lt;/code&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;not atomic&lt;/strong&gt;. The OS truncates the file first, then writes content. If the process is killed mid-write (e.g. SIGKILL, crash), the file is left truncated — all data lost.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This caused nanobot&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;SessionManager.save()&lt;/code&gt; to corrupt session JSONL files on gateway kill, losing all conversation history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="solution-temp-file--atomic-rename"&gt;Solution: Temp File + Atomic Rename&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;
&lt;table style="border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;10
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;11
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;12
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; os&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; tempfile
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;fd, tmp_path &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; tempfile&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;mkstemp(&lt;span style="color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic"&gt;dir&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;target_dir, suffix&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;&amp;#34;.tmp&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; os&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fdopen(fd, &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;&amp;#34;w&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; f:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; f&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;write(data)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; f&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;flush()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; os&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fsync(f&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fileno()) &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"&gt;# ensure data hits disk&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; os&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;replace(tmp_path, target_path) &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"&gt;# atomic on POSIX&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;except&lt;/span&gt; BaseException:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; os&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;unlink(tmp_path) &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"&gt;# cleanup on failure&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;raise&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="key-points"&gt;Key Points&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;os.replace()&lt;/code&gt; is atomic on the same filesystem — either the old file exists OR the new file exists, never a half-written state&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;tempfile.mkstemp(dir=...)&lt;/code&gt; — use same directory to guarantee same filesystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;os.fsync()&lt;/code&gt; ensures data is flushed to disk before rename&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On crash: old file stays intact, temp file is orphaned garbage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On success: old file is replaced atomically&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="when-to-use"&gt;When to Use&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Session/data files that are written periodically&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any file where partial writes = data loss&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Config files that might be written during signal handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>launchd Service Management</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/launchd-service-management/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/launchd-service-management/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Date:&lt;/strong&gt; 2026-04-09
&lt;strong&gt;Context:&lt;/strong&gt; Auto-restart nanobot gateway on crash&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-is-launchd"&gt;What is launchd?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;macOS&amp;rsquo;s native service manager — replaces cron, init.d, supervisord on macOS. It&amp;rsquo;s PID 1, always running, manages all system and user services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="user-agents-vs-system-daemons"&gt;User Agents vs System Daemons&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;User agents&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;code&gt;~/Library/LaunchAgents/&lt;/code&gt; — runs as your user, starts on login&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System daemons&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;code&gt;/Library/LaunchDaemons/&lt;/code&gt; — runs as root, starts on boot&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="key-plist-keys"&gt;Key plist Keys&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;
&lt;table style="border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;10
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;11
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;12
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;13
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;14
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;15
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;16
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;17
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-xml" data-lang="xml"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;KeepAlive&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;true/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"&gt;&amp;lt;!-- auto-restart on crash --&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;RunAtLoad&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;true/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"&gt;&amp;lt;!-- start when loaded --&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;ProgramArguments&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;array&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;/bin/bash&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;/path/to/wrapper.sh&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/array&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;StandardOutPath&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;/path/to/stdout.log&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;StandardErrorPath&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/key&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;/path/to/stderr.log&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;&amp;lt;/string&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="gotcha-environment-variables"&gt;Gotcha: Environment Variables&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;launchd does &lt;strong&gt;NOT&lt;/strong&gt; source &lt;code&gt;.zshrc&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;.bashrc&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;.profile&lt;/code&gt;. Env vars from those files are unavailable.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>LLM Model Fallback Chains</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/llm-model-fallback-chains/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/llm-model-fallback-chains/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Date:&lt;/strong&gt; 2026-04-09
&lt;strong&gt;Context:&lt;/strong&gt; nanobot model fallback when GLM-5.1 overloads&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="problem"&gt;Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LLM providers have rate limits, outages, and overload errors. If your primary model is unavailable, the entire request fails — user gets nothing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="solution-ordered-fallback-list"&gt;Solution: Ordered Fallback List&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Configure a list of models to try in order when the primary fails:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;primary: glm-5.1
fallback: [glm-5-turbo, glm-4.5-air]
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;On error from primary → try glm-5-turbo → try glm-4.5-air → return last error if all fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Resilient JSONL Loading</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/resilient-jsonl-loading/</link><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/resilient-jsonl-loading/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Date:&lt;/strong&gt; 2026-04-09
&lt;strong&gt;Context:&lt;/strong&gt; nanobot session recovery after corruption&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="problem"&gt;Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When loading a JSONL (JSON Lines) file, a single corrupted line causes &lt;code&gt;json.loads()&lt;/code&gt; to throw and the entire load fails — returning &lt;code&gt;None&lt;/code&gt; / empty state, losing all valid data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="solution-skip-bad-lines"&gt;Solution: Skip Bad Lines&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;
&lt;table style="border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt; 9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;10
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;11
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;12
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;13
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;14
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;15
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f"&gt;16
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;messages &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; []
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bad_lines &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; line &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; file:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; line &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; line&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;strip()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;not&lt;/span&gt; line:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; json&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;loads(line)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;except&lt;/span&gt; json&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;JSONDecodeError:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; bad_lines &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"&gt;# skip, don&amp;#39;t abort&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; messages&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;append(data)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; bad_lines:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; logger&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;warning(&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;&amp;#34;Recovered &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt; messages, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c"&gt; corrupted lines&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic"&gt;len&lt;/span&gt;(messages), bad_lines)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="key-points"&gt;Key Points&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JSONL is append-only by nature — early lines are older, later lines are newer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If corruption happens at the end (most common — killed mid-write), all older data is still valid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Even if corruption is in the middle, surrounding data is recoverable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Return &lt;code&gt;None&lt;/code&gt; only if there&amp;rsquo;s zero recoverable data (no messages AND no metadata)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log corruption count for monitoring — frequent corruption signals a deeper write bug&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="pattern-defense-in-depth"&gt;Pattern: Defense in Depth&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pair with atomic writes for full protection:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>SSRF Whitelisting Localhost</title><link>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/ssrf-whitelisting-localhost/</link><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://nanoelbow.github.io/learnings/posts/ssrf-whitelisting-localhost/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Date&lt;/strong&gt;: 2026-04-08
&lt;strong&gt;Context&lt;/strong&gt;: nanobot agent, rederive project&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-is-ssrf"&gt;What is SSRF?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Server-Side Request Forgery. An attacker tricks a server into making HTTP requests to internal resources the attacker can&amp;rsquo;t reach directly. In an AI agent context, a malicious prompt could instruct the agent to fetch &lt;code&gt;http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/&lt;/code&gt; (AWS credentials) or &lt;code&gt;http://localhost:6379/&lt;/code&gt; (Redis).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-nanobot-has-ssrf-protection"&gt;Why nanobot has SSRF protection&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nanobot&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;web_fetch&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;web_search&lt;/code&gt; tools make outbound HTTP requests. Without a guard, any URL — including private/internal addresses — would be fair game. The guard in &lt;code&gt;nanobot/security/network.py&lt;/code&gt; blocks:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>